(557, 687, 54, 1, 0, '1548669220', '.', 'Data transmission through optical fiber there are various types of dispersion occurred for example modal, chromatic and polarization dispersion. As we know these dispersion are not beneficial for our transmission so we have to remove these so that communication between transmitter and receiver side would be successful so that there are some technique which we have to use to compensate the dispersion and some of technique are as: EDFA, DCF, FBG and EDC. There are various parameters which we have to analyze during our research work.', '', '1548681531'),
(558, 685, 54, 1, 0, '1548669243', '.', 'The Integration of QOS trust and social trust could improve the performance of routing in MANETs as both quality and security are very important aspects of such networks. Considering these notes, we developed a trust-based scheme, called TSQRS, in which both components are incorporated. To facilitate reliable parameters during the discovery of on demand environments of MANETs, TSQRS considers three important parameters during the discovery of on demand routes, i.e., channel quality, link residual life and residual energy, to reduce route failures and to increase the overall system performance.', '', '1548682171'),
