(569, 698, 54, 1, 0, '1550474377', '.', 'Adhere to the principles of security, availability, interoperability, and traceability; and gradually establish and improve the basic basis of AI, interoperability, industry applications, network security, privacy protection, and other technical standards. Speed up the promotion of autonomous driving, service robot, and other application sector industry associations in developing relevant standards. Encourage AI enterprises to participate in or lead the development of international standards, and a technical standards going out approach to promote AI products and services in overseas applications. Strengthen the protection of intellectual property in the field of AI, improve the field of AI technology innovation, patent protection, and standardization of interactive support mechanisms to promote the innovation of AI intellectual property rights. Establish AI public patent pools to promote the use of AI and the spread of new technologies.', '', '1551071084'),
(570, 701, 31, 1, 0, '1550814036', '.', 'As per the basepaper attached and the topic mentioned, the work is completely experimental oriented where the electric discharge machining is formulated. As per the research topic, inconel material needs to be used. Here in basepaper, validation is performed based on regression analysis using minitab. \r\n\r\nIf experimental results and procedure is provided from client end we can do the validation with the help of MATLAB software. Please confirm the same.', '', '1551444204'),
(571, 700, 54, 1, 0, '1550814050', '.', 'We suggest to propose new adaptations of evolving Spiking Neural Networks (eSNNs) for online learning scenarios under concept drift. Firstly, we have adapted the traditional eSNN technique to be used on online data streams by limiting the size of the neuron repository, yielding the so-called Online eSNN (OeSNN). Secondly, we have embraced the use of selective and generative data reduction techniques (DRTs) to optimize the contents of the neuron repository so as to achieve a better adaptability of the model to changing concepts over the processed data stream.', '', '1551070885'),
(572, 706, 54, 1, 0, '1550908420', '.', 'A novel ensemble learning method based on multiple deep models, multi-objective optimization algorithm and designed selection strategy is proposed for intelligent fault diagnosis of rotor faults and rolling bearings. The proposed\r\nensemble learning fault diagnosis method includes three main\r\nsteps: Firstly, initialize and train the CRNs, DAEs and DBNs with\r\nrandom structural and learning parameters. Secondly, the MOEA/\r\nDD algorithm is applied to evolve the parameter populations, then\r\nthe newly generated learners with corresponding parameters will\r\nbe trained and tested. Finally, after iterations of evolution, the\r\ncomponent learners in the final population are selectively\r\ncombined to establish the ensemble model for rotor and bearing fault diagnosis. Both accuracy, diversity and training speed are considered in the designed selection strategy and the combination weights are optimized by differential evolution algorithm', '', '1551070815'),
