(614, 754, 54, 1, 0, '1553487904', '.', 'Possible Suggestion:We suggest the tunable loss and effective index waveguides which exploits graphenes controllable optical conductivity.In addition to the advantages associated with the slow group velocity, photonic crystal waveguide modulators are found to exhibit other structural and optoelectronic merits for high speed modulation.The scaling is governed by certain intrinsic optoelectronic properties of silicon and fundamental nature of light, and plays a significant role in determining the minimum ac current density and power of silicon modulators.', '', '1553514819'),
(615, 753, 54, 1, 0, '1553487918', '.', '\r\nPossible suggestion:This optimization or feasibility can be further extended to grid integration issues and battery storage devices in conjunction.a simulation optimization model based on meta-model based hybrid algorithm is developed to find the optimal size of PV, wind and diesel power generator as well as the optimal size of storage system. A hybrid energy system (HES) integrates different energy sources to form a single system such that  the weakness of some energy sources is complemented by the strengths of other energy sources.', '', '1553512667'),
(616, 752, 54, 1, 0, '1553487925', '.', 'Possible Suggestion:  we suggest  the effect of the magnetic field\r\non nanoparticles in the application of epilepsy detection. The\r\nsimulation results show that nanoparticles have been\r\naffected by similar neuronal magnetic field and aggregation\r\nis performed accordingly. Based on different geometry\r\nproduced by neuronal maps, we have shown that\r\nnanoparticle would be trapped inside the closed geometry.\r\nFor monitoring the nanoparticles location, because of\r\nmaximum contrast agent of this nanoparticle, MRI would be\r\nhelpful for discovering the epileptic regions', '', '1553661594'),
(617, 751, 54, 1, 0, '1553487931', '.', 'We suggest to an advanced AP-tree indexing method called AP-tree+ to support continuous\r\nspatial approximate keyword queries with efficiently embedding minimum-wise (min-wise)\r\nsignatures into the AP-tree structure based on one-permutation min-wise hashing. A parallel version of AP-tree+ on a GPU platform, which further improved the performance of our indexing structure for fast processing geo-textual streaming data. The GPU-aided method parallelized the approximate keyword matching of AP-tree+ based on a min-wise parallel hashing algorithm. Further employed a data streaming communication method to optimize I/O overheads\r\nbetween GPU and CPU during continuously processing geo-textual streaming data. and also can suggest to do experimental setup, then evaluated and discussed the performances of AP-Tree+, and the GPU-aided AP-Tree+ against geo-textual streaming data using a NVIDIA GPU.', '', '1553686533'),
(618, 756, 31, 1, 0, '1553579377', '.', 'We can work as per the below basepaper, \"voice conversion of deaf and dumb (1).pdf\".\r\n\r\nHere the possible suggestion is to employ enhanced machine learning classifier other than K NN which can imporve the recognition and conversion rate. Implementation can be carried out in MATLAB', '', '1553687380'),
